#! <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
#! <TRANSFORMER
# TRANSFORMER_BEGIN DCAT_Reader_MB_SK,1,"""FGP Tools""",b4017878-3d65-479b-84b3-e94f2e4e9e27,"Linked by Default",No,NO_PARALLELISM,,No,25241,YES,No,313,No,
# <p><strong>Description</strong></p>
# <p>This Custom Transformer is used to read ESRI GeoHub DCAT server.  GeoHub DCAT reader is using two server extractions (a primary and a secondary) to extract a complete set of DCAT metadata for each record.  Metadata extracted from the primary server extracttion are prefixed wirh <em>DCAT_P</em> whereas the the metadata extracted from the secondary server extraction are prefixed with <em>DCAT_S</em>.  In order to join the metadata from the primary and the secondary extraction both extraction must share a common identifier when no common identifier are found the is no secondary metadata with the prfix <em>DCAT_S</em>.</p>
# <p>Note: There is no option to read only one record with a specific identifier.</p>
# <p><strong>Input Ports</strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>Input: One feature to start the extraction of all the records from the GeoHub DCAT server.</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Output Ports</strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>Résultats: All the records read from the GeoHub DCAT server.</li>
# </ul>
# <p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>
# <ul>
# <li>GEO_HUB_SERVICE: Name of the DCAT servers to use. Choices are:<ul>
# <li>Manitoba GeoHub: To read Manitoba GeoHub;</li>
# <li>Saskatchewan GeoHub: To read Sakatchewan GeoHub;</li>
# <li>Custom GeoHub: To enter specific values of primary and secondary url;</li>
# </ul>
# </li>
# <li>CUSTOM_PRIMARY: Definition of the primary Geo Hub service. Used when the option <em>Custom GeoHub</em> is selected;</li>
# <li>CUSTOM_SECONDARY: Definition of the seconary Geo Hub service. Used when the option <em>Custom GeoHub</em> is selected.  It is possible to leave this field empty, in that case no secondary service will be read and less metadata will be extracted.</li>
# </ul>
# TRANSFORMER_END
#!   A0_PREVIEW_IMAGE="data:image/png;base64,"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY="ARCGIS_AUTO"
#!   ATTR_TYPE_ENCODING="SDF"
